Global Infrastructure Eyeing Hochtief Auction, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   E r i k   L a r s o n
-- 
2011-06-19T08:48:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-19/global-infrastructure-eyeing-hochtief-auction-sunday-times-says.html
Global Infrastructure Partners, the
owner of  London ’s Gatwick airport, is considering bidding on
 Hochtief AG (HOT) ’s airport business, the Sunday Times reported,
without saying where it got the information.  Hochtief’s planned $2.3 billion auction includes its stakes
in six facilities, including Sydney airport, plus 40 percent of
Athens airport, the  newspaper  reported. Other interested buyers
include French construction company  Vinci SA (DG)  and Frankfurt
airport owner Fraport AG, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Larson in London at 
 elarson4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 